{"title":"2022 Orbea Occam LT adds a 150mm trail bike into the mix, convertible to 140mm","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/16/2022-orbea-occam-lt-adds-a-150mm-trail-bike-into-the-mix-convertible-to-140mm/","date":1631800838000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam m ltd top end model\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111432/2022-orbea-occam-lt-m-ltd-model.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271670\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The Orbea Occam has evolved numerous times over last few years, graduating from the 120mm TR with flexible stays, to the 140mm 29er trail bike with a pivot concentric to the rear axle. Along the way, we’ve seen the introduction of that asymmetric front triangle, longer travel all-mountain versions, with subtle changes to the rear suspension platform throughout. For 2022, the Orbea Occam is back in two travel configurations; 140mm front and rear (like the 2020 Occam) and a new 150mm travel LT version. What’s more, you can now switch between the two.</p><h2>2022 Orbea Occam</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam 140mm 29er trail bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111446/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-140mm-trail-bike-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>For 2022, the Orbea Occam doesn’t see much of an overhaul. The geometry, asymmetric frame design and ride kinematic remain largely unchanged, still running their Concentric Boost 2 suspension linkage wherein there’s a pivot concentric to the rear axle.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam m ltd suspension linkage concentric boost 2\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15113613/2022-orbea-occam-m-ltd-suspension-linkage-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The claimed merits of the linkage are that the suspension is still able to remain active under braking. It’s still a 140mm travel 29er trail bike.&nbsp;</p><div id=\"attachment_271704\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271704\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam m 10 lt 150mm 29er trail bike purple fox dhx2 coil shock\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111442/2022-orbea-occam-m10-lt-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271704\">The 2022 Orbea Occam LT runs 150mm travel front and rear, with air and coil shock options and 4-piston brakes</p></div><p>The news here is that, for 2022, Orbea have released the Occam LT, a 150mm travel option. It’s not the first time the Occam has seen 150mm rear wheel travel; the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2016/03/10/review-orbea-occam-am-m-ltd-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">AM version of 2016</a> had as much, but that was delivered through a suspension design that used flex stays.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea ccam lt jump\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111437/2022-orbea-occam-lt-pruple-coil-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>With 10mm additional travel in the front and rear, the bike is definitely more geared towards descending. The geometry is slightly slacker, with a 66.5° head angle versus the 66° HA of the 140mm. The seat tube is 0.5° slacker too at 76.5°, though that’s not something to get too hung up on given that you can likely counter that by pushing the saddle forward on the rails.</p><div id=\"attachment_271706\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271706\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam lt leverage curve\" width=\"1600\" height=\"853\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves-297x158.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves-800x427.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves-120x64.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves-768x409.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111718/2022-orbea-occam-lt-leverage-curves-1536x819.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271706\">The 140mm and 150mm travel Occam have a near identical leverage curve</p></div><p>Both versions of the Occam are available in sizes S-XL with reach spanning a 425mm to 500mm range, covering rider heights of 150cm to 198cm. Chainstays come in at 440mm, consistent across the frame sizes.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam lt geometry chart\" width=\"1600\" height=\"757\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart-297x141.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart-800x379.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart-120x57.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart-768x363.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15104257/2022-orbea-occam-lt-geometry-chart-1536x727.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Can you convert between the 140mm and 150mm travel versions? Yes! All you need to do is swap out the shock and fork. The shock’s eye-to-eye length is the same (210mm) – the LT just runs a longer stroke (55mm).</p><p>You might also be wondering whether you can boost the travel on your <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/06/17/all-new-orbea-occam-reshaped-into-long-slack-all-mountain-ready-trail-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">2020 Occam</a> to 150mm. Sadly, that’s not possible. Apparently there is a risk that the would come into contact with the frame. The new Occam has a slightly different top tube (sizes S and M) to accommodate this.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam lt 150mm coil shock\" width=\"1600\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm-297x99.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm-800x267.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm-120x40.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm-768x256.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15114054/2022-orbea-occam-lt-150mm-1536x512.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>In keeping with the additional travel of the LT and its more aggresive geometry, the spec is tailored appropriately. While the 140mm Occam gets 2-Piston brakes with 180mm rotors, a FOX DPX shock and a FOX 34 fork, the Occam LT gets 4-piston brakes with a 203mm front rotor, the option to run a FOX X2 Air shock or the DHX2 Coil version, paired with a FOX 36 fork. The bikes’ differing intentions are reflected in the tires too; the 140mm gets a Maxxis High Roller and Rekon combo while the LT gets a Minion DHF and Dissector pairing.</p><div id=\"attachment_271700\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271700\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing.jpg\" alt=\"2022 orbea occam flp multitool pivot magnet storage\" width=\"1600\" height=\"747\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing-297x139.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing-800x374.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing-120x56.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing-768x359.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/15111425/2022-orbea-occam-flp-multitool-pivot-magnetic-housing-1536x717.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271700\">Like the new <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/10/2022-orbea-rallon-gets-mullet-option-heaps-of-frame-storage-and-new-geometry/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Orbea Rallon</a> released last week, the 2022 Occam gets a four-function multitool housed inside the main pivot axle, held in place by a magnet</p></div><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The 2022 Orbea Occam (140mm) is available in both OMR Carbon and aluminium (Hydro) complete builds. Pricing for complete carbon bikes starts at $4,299 USD, whereas the alloy options are much more affordable starting at $2,999 USD.&nbsp;</p><p>The Occam LT is only available with the OMR Carbon frameset; pricing starts at $4,599 USD.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://www.orbea.com/us-en/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Orbea.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"fd8329912e9645c21c237663171e1b9435bdb09505157322267f66a6f380923a","category":"Cycling"}